---
layout: layout.njk
permalink: /forensics/index.html
title: Forensics
description: Sanitized technical evidence and audit limitations.
---
<section class="hero compact">
  <p class="eyebrow">Evidence before certainty</p>
  <h1>Forensics</h1>
  <p class="lede">A public evidence trail that keeps method, observation time, and confidence while excluding raw captures and private infrastructure.</p>
</section>
<section aria-label="Forensic findings">
  <div class="timeline">
    {% for item in audit.forensics %}
    <article class="timeline-item">
      <span class="timeline-index">{{ loop.index | twoDigit }}</span>
      <div>
        <h2>{{ item.label }}</h2>
        <p class="metric-value small">{{ item.value }} <span>{{ item.unit }}</span></p>
        <p>{{ item.interpretation }}</p>
        <p class="source-line"><strong>Source:</strong> {{ item.source }} · <strong>Confidence:</strong> {{ item.confidence }}</p>
      </div>
    </article>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
<section class="panel limitation" aria-labelledby="limits-title">
  <p class="eyebrow">Important boundary</p>
  <h2 id="limits-title">What this public edition does not claim</h2>
  <p>The sample is deliberately narrow. It does not estimate business performance, user intent, realized impact, or population-wide behavior. Recommendations require controlled validation before production decisions.</p>
</section>

